text: Martine de Souza (born 26 July 1973) is a Mauritian badminton player. She competed in women's singles and women's doubles at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona, and in three events at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1973 births Category:Living people Category:Mauritian female badminton players Category:Olympic badminton players of Mauritius Category:Badminton players at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Badminton players at the 1996 Summer Olympics
